Two weeks ago I warned about the financial media's confident bullishness that was apparently based on one day's reversal of -26 S&P handles to breakeven. Citing sound full of fury signifying nothing I warned that the next four days of downward reversals (not addressed

by the bullish cabal) suggested a changing mkt complexion,was perhaps more significant. I also stated that we will never hear a mea cupla from the bulls. I was correct on both fronts. @tomkeene @SquawkCNBC @CNBCFastMoney @michaelsantoli They know and we know who they are.
I would like to think they have learned but we know better. More lessons learned. We all get market wrong but too few face up to their hubris and forecasts when they are dead wrong.
